reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You have to reset your dishwasher after install!!
reviews.reviewText: My old element burnt out so I ordered this one. I thought it was junk as the dishwasher would not clean and it never seemed to be heating water. Today I was searching for a oem element to replace it and stumbled on a post of someone saying you need to reset the dishwasher after install. Turns out dishwashers throw codes like cars and have a full diagnostic mode, after reset this element is working perfect. Search whirlpool dishwasher reset and follow instructions, it's an easy process and necessary for the element to work.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars fit my whorlpool dishwasher - had to spring them to match the wholes
reviews.reviewText: the element in my dishwasher had failed - dishwasher had a diagnostic that indicated that there was a problem heating. ordered this an an over-temp switch - no visible signs of burnt element- put an ohm meter on the element and it read open circuit - the new element read about ~50 ohms. Element came with plastic nuts that secured it - original element had a little bit of sealant on the threads I used blue removable lock tight. Snugged it up - it had a brass and rubber gland on the water side - units did not leak on install - dishwasher repaired.
